# Environment Rules

- All secrets/config in .env file at project root
- .env is gitignored — never commit it
- .env.example has every variable with comments explaining how to get the value
- Access env vars in backend via process.env.VARIABLE_NAME
- If a required env var is missing, log a clear error message and exit gracefully
- Never log the actual values of API keys or tokens — only log their presence/absence
- The Google refresh token is stored in tokens.json (gitignored) at project root
- Ollama has no API key — it's just a local HTTP server

## Required .env variables (all must exist):
OLLAMA_BASE_URL, OLLAMA_MODEL, GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET,
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI, SLACK_BOT_TOKEN, SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET,
OBSIDIAN_API_URL, OBSIDIAN_API_KEY, PORT, SESSION_SECRET
